<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="334" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,463,1533]" pageId="3" pageNumber="334">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,535,560]" pageId="3" pageNumber="334">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(Female unknown): Dorsal shield elongated, ridge on dorsal shield apically tapering; P-4 with well developed ventral projection, curved, directed anteriorly; I-III-L claws with comb-like ventral clawlets; IV-L-6 slender, with two small terminal setae and a row of three stronger sub-terminal setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,463,1533]" pageId="3" pageNumber="334">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,365,644,669]" pageId="3" pageNumber="334">Description—</emphasis>
Idiosoma oval; dorsal shield elongated, L/W 503/350, ratio 1.44, anteriorly rounded, ridge on dorsal shield apically bluntly pointed, caudally dissolved, glandularia far laterally (
<figureCitation box="[1104,1196,679,704]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1839,1861]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,196,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1818]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Platymamersopsis mayottensis sp. nov., male, Koualé River, Mayotte: A = dorsal shield; B = ventral; C = IV-L-5 and -6; D = I-L; E = palp. Scale bars = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1437788/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="334">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); ventral shield (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1839,1861]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,196,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1818]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Platymamersopsis mayottensis sp. nov., male, Koualé River, Mayotte: A = dorsal shield; B = ventral; C = IV-L-5 and -6; D = I-L; E = palp. Scale bars = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1437788/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="334">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
) oval, L/W 541/438; coxal field L/W 297/356, anteriorly extending beyond frontal margin, medial margin of Cx-I long (mL 70), medial margin of Cx-III mid-sized (mL 36), mL Cx-I/Cx-III ratio 1.9; Cxgl-2 close to posterior margin of Cx-II, Cxgl-4 at anterior margin of Cx-III; Cx-IV posteriorly and laterally rounded, dorso-laterally extended to the level of Cx-II. Genital field L/W 103/100, rounded, laterally smoothly convex, posteriorly slightly extended beyond genital bay; acetabula mid-sized, L Ac-1-3: 28, 28, 31; a few small setae present on genital flaps; setae of Vgl-1 posterior to caudal corner of Cx-IV, Vgl-3 close to caudo-lateral margin of Cx-IV; excretory pore and Vgl-2 close together, distanced from the posterior margin of ventral shield.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,463,1533]" pageId="3" pageNumber="334">
Palp: total L 214, dL/H, dL/H ratio: P-1, 19/43, 0.44; P-2, 83/57, 1.45; P-3, 34/42, 0.82; P-4, 55/33, 1.67; P-5, 23/14, 1.66; P-2/P-4 ratio 1.5; P-2 compact, dorsal margin curved, ventral margin slightly concave, ventral seta mid-sized, pointed; P-4 ventral projection well developed, curved, flanked by a fine subterminal seta (
<figureCitation box="[1290,1377,1039,1064]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1839,1861]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,196,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1818]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Platymamersopsis mayottensis sp. nov., male, Koualé River, Mayotte: A = dorsal shield; B = ventral; C = IV-L-5 and -6; D = I-L; E = palp. Scale bars = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1437788/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="334">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
); P-5 with a strong distal claw flanked by two shorter claws.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,463,1533]" pageId="3" pageNumber="334">
Legs: Due to the fixation all claws retracted in claw sheath, but comb-like clawlets can be observed; dL of I-L: 52, 63, 56, 81, 86, 106; dL of IV-L-4-6: 83, 98, 105; IV-L-6 slender, with two small terminal setae and a row of three stronger sub-terminal setae (
<figureCitation box="[532,621,1183,1208]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1839,1861]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,196,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1818]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Platymamersopsis mayottensis sp. nov., male, Koualé River, Mayotte: A = dorsal shield; B = ventral; C = IV-L-5 and -6; D = I-L; E = palp. Scale bars = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1437788/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="334">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
